Which insurance companies paid dividends during the Great Depression?

It is difficult to provide a definitive answer regarding which specific insurance companies paid dividends during the Great Depression due to numerous factors such as company size, financial performance, and industry regulations. Keep in mind that these were exceptional circumstances, and it's essential to thoroughly research any insurer before investing or purchasing coverage.
